TSO provides development of Linked Data user-interfaces and APIs, based on our OpenUp® platform, that allow public sector bodies to achieve Level 5 Public Sector Transparency Board Principles and open data standards. TSO allows you to capture, transform and deliver your data in the most efficient way. Our team of talented developers can help you get the most from your data sources. We have already delivered a range of projects for our clients, including the creation of APIs to access open data in the cloud. Prices start from £550 per day. TSO is the Public Sector division of Williams Lea, a DHL Supply Chain company and a member of the global Deutsche Post DHL Group.

Multizone's "Workforce Online Social Engagement branded mobile app as a Service" (bSaaS) is a customer branded set of mobile applications for Android, iOS and BlackBerry provided as a service with information about the customer and its workforces activities including what's happening right now provided from open data and social networks without the need to join or log in to anything although replying and engaging with our app content may require a login. Our apps deliver proven engagement to the majority of the community who have mobile phones - a much wider demographic than traditional engagement methods like meetings and circulars, and at a much lower cost. The apps are typically free to download from the mobile phone app stores and are advert free. Features include interaction, social data, open data feeds, maps, activity ratings and push notifications to end users interested in the activities of the customer organisation and itw workforce.

column2: ArcGIS Online is a Geographic Information System (GIS) in the cloud. It is also a content management system for location based data. ArcGIS Online enables you to create and share maps, mapping applications and location services so that you, your colleagues and partners can view, interact with and understand your data in a new way. The maps and applications can include your own data, documents and images and information from other organisations. You can also access maps and aerial and satellite images from other providers. With ArcGIS Online, you can: • Create and share interactive maps that can be accessed through a web browser, Microsoft Office, a mobile device (Android, iOS and Windows), other mapping systems or a custom application • Access and discover free maps, datasets, services, tools and other geospatial content • Manage your geospatial content through an easy-to-use catalogue of items and groups • Share your content publicly, or with specific groups, or keep it private • Carry out geoprocessing tasks such as geocoding, routing and real time feeds • Use pre-defined templates and layouts to quickly publish location information • Stay in control of your data, lower your IT costs, and provide your internal users, partners and the public with easy-to-use, web-enabled content • Integrate with your organisation’s security system (e.g. Active Directory) to control access to your data. ArcGIS Online can help provide information on public services by providing access to key information, allowing the sharing of information between organisations, and assisting with issues relating to accountability and transparency, including published Open Data on data.gov.uk and similar sites.

EPC provides the management and hosting of appliances within the Oracle Engineered System portfolio. IL0 Service and pricing is currently available for Atos Database Services - Oracle on Exadata which is located in mainland Europe. Additional services such as Atos Business Analytics, Oracle on Exalytics and Atos Server Management, Oracle on Exalogic are available on request from Atos. There will be both IL0 and IL3 services available in 2013 (pending G-Cloud accreditation).
The objective of Atos Database Services - Oracle on Exadata is to provide a client with a dedicated managed operational environment for Oracle databases and to ensure that committed service levels are met. Oracle Exadata is a preconfigured Oracle Database machine including:
	Database servers within the Oracle Database Machine;
	Storage servers (including SAS/SATA/Flash Disk Storage) within the Oracle Database Machine;
	InfiniBand Network between the database servers and storage servers within the Oracle Database Machine;
	Oracle GRID infrastructure.
Atos provides maintenance of the Exadata appliance and manages the databases hosted on the platform.
Appropriate network connections can be made to allow both citizen/customer access, and civil servant/staff access, to the services.

Important characteristics:
Location Choice - Mainland Europe or UK based:
EPC allows the decision of where the hosting is located, either mainland Europe @ IL0 or data can be held and processed within UK ListX data centres to meet key UK security requirements (ie IL3). 
Data is not sent or held off-shore
Processing is not carried out off-shore
Secure:  Environments will be certified to the appropriate UK impact level and the option for data and device retention is available
Cleared: Operations staff can be UK Security cleared (if required)
Automated:  Atos manages the infrastructure with a very high level of software tooling, including remote monitoring and automatic alerting
Atos manages the EPC environments in accordance to ISO 9001 and ISO 27001 standards.
Atos believes this enables delivery at UK CESG Impact Levels 0, 1, 2 and 3.
Customers have a choice of appliance capacity sizes to ensure that the footprint meets their needs.

column2:
Technical consulting and development using open source technologies

We specialise in developing services that consume or publish data via APIs. We develop custom RESTful APIs for clients who wish to publish their own data. We integrate data from other cloud-based systems with expertise in many different APIs, data sources and formats, including RSS, XML, JSON, SOAP and REST. 

For clients who need to create their own cloud-based applications we can develop small-scale, custom PHP web and mobile-web applications. These projects normally combine development services with our agile web project management, user-interface design and information architecture consulting.

All our development work uses object-oriented PHP, with a preference for MVC frameworks such as Zend Framework and CodeIgnitor. For projects with a cloud-based content management component, we specialise in the SilverStripe open-source web content management system (CMS) and MVC framework (see www.silverstripe.org).

We advise and consult on open-source hosting infrastructure, specifically the Linux/Apache/PHP/MySQL stack.
column315: Technical Consulting, Open Data APIs and PHP Web Development

column2: The Data Services as a Service enables data stored in legacy/operational systems, in the cloud and on-premise, to be exposed as a web service and publish via the Cloud as an API. And provides a platform for big data repository and analysis. It is the basis for enablement of e-Government allowing collaboration and re-use of the existing systems/processes and the orchestration of new services/business processes. APIs are exposed in a controlled and secure manner. Data access is provided without ever having to open up databases to networks or the cloud. One of the key initiatives that can be supported is open data – making public sector data accessible on the internet through a secure and manageable process. Data Services support a number of business use cases including: * Open Data * Enterprise Application Integration * Master Data Management * Operational Intelligence * Content Management/Electronic Data Management * Mobile and Web Applications The embedded MongoDB database supports a NoSQL model to deliver highly flexible, high performance and scalable data management platform in support of agile service delivery, mobile application delivery and web application delivery. Performance is improved by 20 times and storage requirements reduced by as much as 90%. Data Services as a Service includes a leading content management and workflow system that is based on open source technologies including Apache, PHP and Django. This has quickly become one of the leading CMS in the fashion industry. We have now adapted the solution for the G-Cloud and focus to bring solutions to the UK Public Sector. Important consideration is that at the termination (or end of 1 or 2 year call-off contract term) the customer owns the data and the applications. As this solution is built with open source there will be no on-going software maintenance fees or one time license costs in event the customer wishes to bring on-premise. With typical IT systems lifespan 7-10 years this represents a major cost advantage compared to proprietary software offerings.

As organisers of the Digpen grassroots network for designers and developers in the South West, we run both commercial and non-commercial design and development events, including conferences, workshops, design jams and hackdays (hackathons). 

Hack days and design jam events help organisations explore solutions to specific business, customer or user problems by bringing together designers, developers and subject-matter experts to brainstorm and rapidly prototype ideas. Hack days are ideal for testing APIs and cloud-based open data services, creating proofs of concept around data sets prior to more substantial API development, and building a developer community around your data feeds and services.

We can help with
	On-the-day organisation and event management
	Team facilitation
	Working with stakeholders and subject matter experts to craft challenges
	Evaluating and cleaning up your existing data sources
	Finding and liaising with venues
	Event marketing and publicity
	Sponsorship
	AV support, including recording and podcasting

column2: TSO Data Enrichment Service (DES) processes text and extracts information via web-based APIs, which can be linked to external data sources. The DES is part of the OpenUp® platform of services that can Harvest, Enrich, Store and Publish your data as Open Linked Data. The DES can be used to create linked open data or as a standalone service. It is one of a range of semantic web tools, making data discoverable. The DES processes open standard formats, plain text, HTML and XML documents, and can output XML, RDFa, RDF/XML or HTML and JSON, also XHTML+RDFa adding mark up to the original content. TSO is the Public Sector division of Williams Lea, a DHL Supply Chain company and a member of the global Deutsche Post DHL Group.

Digirati provides strategy, design, integration and engineering consultancy to public and private sector clients for online publishing and customer engagement solutions. Our approach and methodology is highly disciplined, lean and agile to ensure high value implementations that deliver to a well-considered set of requirements We utilise open source technologies where appropriate to avoid vendor lock in for our customers and better collaboration with other bodies when possible. Digirati run a number of open source projects themselves which are used on multiple engagements including a solution for delivering library content over the web and an interactive timeline that works with Linked Data. We are also a Gold Partner for the open source Umbraco CMS. Our development approach is Agile and platform-centric. Reliable technical delivery of well-architected systems is what Digirat's reputation is built upon. Our work is 100% onshore and we work onsite as much as required during the build phase using iterative development techniques to ensure a regular feedback loop with the client. Our engineers are specially selected to have strong communication skills and a customer focus based on the principle of the "true engineer": an engineer that can talk to a client, understand their requirements and devise and deliver a solution. This is a cost-effective direct approach which ensures quality and cuts out unnecessary and expensive project overheads. We engage with clients at every stage of a project lifespan from research and analysis to design, implementation and support. Digirati's full set of services can be categorised as follows: Digital Strategy Business Analysis User Experience Visual Design User Interface Design System Architecture Agile Software Development System Integration Testing Training Support Hosting Project Management Digirati have worked with a large number of central government departments such as the Home Office, UK Border Agency, Communities & Local Government, Ofcom, MOJ, HMI Probation, and the Welsh Assembly; typically focusing on the technical implementation of their content managed websites and online systems with various bespoke developments and integrations. The value we bring to our clients is driven by our belief that well aligned technology reduces the ongoing costs of digital projects. Typical solution domains that we build and integrate include: Web, Mobile & Tablet Content Delivery Multichannel Content Management Enterprise Search Semantic Web, Linked Data & Open Data Knowledge Organisation Systems Access Control & Rights Management Online Communities, Social Media & Collaboration Solutions Web & Social Media Analytics Impact Level 0, however with numerous software certifications in place as well as compliance with both ISO9001 and ISO27001 we ensure the highest quality and security of the work we deliver.

column2: CKAN is a powerful data management system to publish open government data. It is used by various national governments and public institutions around the world, like data.gov.uk, data.gov, and the EU open data portal (see also www.ckan.org/instances). WHY CKAN? Some core characteristics make it a perfect choice for any public sector institution: CKAN.org is a community-based open source project and the source code is AGPL v3 licensed. This open approach assures users maximum room for manoeuvre in the future, protects their investment and prevents vendor lock-in. CKAN’s architecture is highly modular: components and extensions allow the system to be customized to your needs. Developers can easily extend its functionality without the need to understand the whole system. In addition, CKAN offers a rich RESTful API (using JSON representations) that exposes all of CKAN’s core functionality to external client applications using only open web standards. Finally, CKAN adheres to open standards ensuring interoperability like INSPIRE, OGC CSW, metadata based on DCAT, as well as HTML and web services based on REST. FEATURES. CKAN supports publishers and data re-users alike. Publishers benefit from easy metadata management, workflow and approval support, user authorization, the reporting of broken links, and analytics and use stats. Re-users benefit from a long list of search and discovery features, like powerful search/filtering incl. “following” datasets, faceted browsing by tags/publishers/keywords/etc., a data explorer that allows preview, inspection and basic graphing for many types of data. In addition, CKAN offers INSPIRE-compliant geospatial capabilities like geo-search, map visualization, and metadata schemas (ISO19139, Gemini2.1, CSW); harvesting and normalization of metadata from other catalogs/servers from a variety of servers (CKAN, ArcGIS, Geoportal, Z39.50, WAF, CSW); data catalog interoperability (Data Catalog Interoperability Protocol) allowing search across different catalogs; multilingual support. SERVICE. If you are running a CKAN-based open data portal, we can offer the full range of support services: from general maintenance and support up to bespoke development of extensions (, e.g., dashboards or visualisations) and customizations tailored to your needs. Technical support days may be bought individually at £890 / day (including both project management and collaborative technical support) or in blocks of 10 days-plus (usable within 12 months) at £8,300 per 10-day block. Support days may include for example: Consultancy / advice – on data portals, functionality and open data policy; Custom development – for example, integrating with another service, development of new features, customisation of input forms and schemas, and site theming; Support / upgrades – technical support for CKAN and upgrades to new versions; Bug fixing – quickly resolving any issues with your deployment. As all core maintainers of CKAN are working for the Open Knowledge Foundation, we can provide the complete technical know-how about CKAN in-house. Instead of a trial/free option, you can always approach the CKAN community directly online with your questions/requests. Key words: open data portal, open data management, datahub, ckan.org, socrata, data visualization, extension, customization, API, linked data, tag vocabulary, filestore, datastore, web interface, notification, schema, apps, JSON , XML, RDF

column2: In its Open Data White Paper "Unleashing the Potential" the Government outlined its serious intent to make public sector data more available to businesses and to the public. Deloitte will help departments to deliver this by capturing a clear understanding of their data's current availability and the actions needed to increase that availability. This may be used to assist portfolio planning or support business case development. The White Paper stated a principle that organisations should “Release data quickly, and then work to make sure that it is available in open standard formats, including linked-data forms.” The industry standard for measuring data availability is the 'Five Stars of Linked Open Data', specified by Sir Tim Berbers-Lee. The pinnacle of availability is considered to be a 5 star 'linked data' rating which indicates that the data is both available and is already linked to other data sources; allowing it to be easily exploited to generate insight. It may not be practical or good value for money to attempt to make all of an organisation's data meet this standard. To make meaningful progress, each department will need to understand where their gaps are, the ones to focus on that will drive the greatest value and the practical steps they can take to resolve these gaps. Deloitte will guide the client through this process, using a standardised approach, drawing on our extensive experience of data quality, data management and data transformation. We will also bring industry leading experts to this process from our excellent contacts in academia.

column2: The non-profit Open Knowledge Foundation (founded 2004) promotes open data and open content in all its forms, in domains ranging from government and science to culture. Its approach is hands-on, developing real solutions, ranging from open source software tools to training materials to connecting communities through working groups, to strategy consultancy for data publishers. The OKF has deployed or enabled others to deploy a large set of more than 50 digital data repositories around the world (ckan.org/instances). They run on software developed by the OKF, and range from every level of government to NGOs and community-driven portals. Our consultancy services cover the complete process of opening up data - from initial vision/policy work to data publication processes. Unique to OKF’s offering is that we can simultaneously address the supply side and the demand side (data re-users). Please refer to the service description for a more detailed, process-based description of our consulting offer.

column2: This service consists of the provision of data analytics to inform strategy and policy development. It is designed for organisations which collect or have access to a large volume of structured and unstructured data and wish to systematically analyse this in order to derive policy- and business-relevant insights. This service comprises of a range of bespoke analytical tools including business intelligence, data management, econometrics, geo-spatial and visualisation analyses. Deloitte would work with you to identify your exam question and how data analytics could be applied to derive new and valuable insights. These tools can be used across all sectors and departments, covering issues such as driving efficiencies, stimulating innovation, maximising value for money, achieving policy outcomes and identifying problems before they arise. These tools can draw on both open data and data held privately by organisations. The results can be encoded into easy-to-use visualisation tools that can be rolled out across organisations. This is designed as a one-off service whereby Deloitte would build the model/tool for the initial analysis and hand over to you for continuing maintenance and upgrading. The time frame for the service would vary according to your requirement, but could take at least six months - though this is highly contingent on data quality and the complexity of the exam question.

Digirati provides strategy, design, integration and engineering consultancy to public and private sector clients for online publishing and customer engagement solutions. Our approach and methodology is highly disciplined, lean and agile to ensure high value implementations that deliver to a well-considered set of requirements
We utilise open source technologies where appropriate to avoid vendor lock in for our customers and better collaboration with other bodies when possible. Digirati run a number of open source projects themselves which are used on multiple engagements including a solution for delivering library content over the web and an interactive timeline that works with Linked Data. We are also a Gold Partner for the open source Umbraco CMS.
Our development approach is Agile and platform-centric. Reliable technical delivery of well-architected systems is what Digirat's reputation is built upon. Our work is 100% onshore and we work onsite as much as required during the build phase using iterative development techniques to ensure a regular feedback loop with the client. Our engineers are specially selected to have strong communication skills and a customer focus based on the principle of the "true engineer": an engineer that can talk to a client, understand their requirements and devise and deliver a solution. This is a cost-effective direct approach which ensures quality and cuts out unnecessary and expensive project overheads.
We engage with clients at every stage of a project lifespan from research and analysis to design, implementation and support. Digirati's full set of services can be categorised as follows:

Digital Strategy
Business Analysis
User Experience
Visual Design
User Interface Design
System Architecture
Agile Software Development
System Integration
Testing
Training
Support
Hosting
Project Management

Digirati have worked with a large number of central government departments such as the Home Office, UK Border Agency, Communities & Local Government, Ofcom, MOJ, HMI Probation, and the Welsh Assembly; typically focusing on the technical implementation of their content managed websites and online systems with various bespoke developments and integrations.
The value we bring to our clients is driven by our belief that well aligned technology reduces the ongoing costs of digital projects. Typical solution domains that we build and integrate include:

Web, Mobile & Tablet Content Delivery
Multichannel Content Management
Enterprise Search
Semantic Web, Linked Data & Open Data
Knowledge Organisation Systems
Access Control & Rights Management
Online Communities, Social Media & Collaboration
Solutions Web & Social Media Analytics

With numerous software certifications in place as well as compliance with both ISO9001 and ISO27001 we ensure the highest quality and security of the work we deliver.

column2: This package is targeted at buyers with the challenge of transitioning their current architectures to enable Agile Development and facilitate lean methods of working adopting cloud based approaches where appropriate. It helps to define the organisational objectives and need as well the various touch/transition points that will be required to undertake the evolution of the current state of Business, Application, Infrastructure and Data architectures to their required target state. Enterprise Blueprints offer a range of output based Agile Technical Architecture, Enterprise Architecture, Technical Strategy and Solution Architecture packages that offer very practical and conformant solutions with excellent Value For Money (VFM). These products are designed to support development of HM Treasury business cases and take account of HMG IT Strategy including GDS’s implementation policy. The scope of the ‘Initial Assessment’ package comprises tailored elements of: • IT Landscape review including options for consolidation, rationalisation and modernisation • Assessment of business architecture maturity • High level assessment of alignment between business and technical/solution architectures • High level assessment of security and compliance architecture • Review of transition from available ‘as-is’ to ‘to-be’ architectures including the use of open source and open standards to address cost and vendor lock-in • The use of modern infrastructure architectures to enable green IT and flexible service provision through cloud based solutions • The development of an assessment of the alignment between the business, technical architectures and the overarching information management strategy and information architecture which could enable provision of open data and use of big data Package delivery is within 4 weeks of commissioning and is based on the assumption that there will be requisite access to client information and parties. An accelerated delivery option can be offered but would attract a 10 to 20% premium depending on circumstances. The results of the assessment can be delivered in a presentation style, or as a formal report depending on the buyers need. The package will include a fixed price, outcome based proposal that provides options to secure the ‘next stage’ work-package and identify a tailored approach to addressing relevant issues for the business. Enterprise Blueprints has experience of conducting agile technical architecture work in IL3 environments and has created very practical outputs that has enabled clients to readily adopt novel initiatives and technical concepts delivered by agile, non-agile and hybrid methodologies, for example: • Technology and service roadmaps that exploit agile development opportunities • Integrated technology based services using ‘SIAM’ coordinated commodity tower sourcing • Migration of legacy environments to service oriented delivery • Intelligent adoption of new technology (cloud, big data, social media, ... ) including assisted digital and providing services aligned to the digital service standard • Operation under exacting compliance including: DPA, ICO, PCI/DSS, ISO27001/HMG IAMM and using frameworks such as ITIL V3 • Technological change as a means of gaining efficiency savings transition to increased green capability and delivery of flexible infrastructure provision If required, solution design and implementation assurance services can be separately offered. Enterprise Blueprints use a blend of experienced consultants and a range of highly competent and innovative architects to ensure products are qualitatively sound and have practical relevance. Every package will benefit from the use of industry leading methods, aligning to the Agile agenda, standardised processes and tooling that are integrated within an accredited quality management system, including: • Strong governance which will be linked to the Client’s to ensure proper control • Industry standard architecture frameworks such as TOGAF, ITIL V3 • Qualified and competent in EA practice(s) evidenced by TOGAF and ITIL Certification and knowledgeable on HMG processes, governance and strategy implementation • Tooling that is available ‘on demand’ and is extensible for client use Each client will have a senior EB architect assigned as being responsible for all aspects of their account and direct access to an Enterprise Blueprints board member in the unlikely event that escalation is necessary.

column2: At Zennor Consulting we provide specialist advice, by security cleared consultants with a track record of delivery within central and local government for organisations looking to adopt or integrate cloud based solutions, which are increasingly being supplied by G-Cloud suppliers. Business Analysis: At the very early stages we can assist with the project concept, seeking to ensure your concept is "cloud ready" and that important issues are understood, such as the business impact levels of data and any pre-existing platforms that might need to be integrated or supported. This leads on to requirements gathering, whilst both the spirit of G-Cloud and Agile ways of working do not embrace writing long lists of requirements up-front, there are still some important key criteria to get down on paper, such as business impact levels, estimated usage, integration requirements or "must have" functionality. Project Selection and Specification: Selection of providers via G-Cloud is becoming more straightforward, however we can still help in running sifting through the service definitions, accreditation status and pricing tables in order to help with long listing, short listing and any detail required to identify the provider that most suits your project needs. Design Authority: The cloud and G-Cloud open up a lot of opportunities regarding solutions, but the architecture within cloud solutions still needs to be defined correctly for any specific project and this is another area where we can help. This might involve meshing two or more cloud providers together, such as CDN and Web Hosting, designing in service separation so that services degrade gracefully under load or failure, or using cloud based testing and monitoring services to ensure the service scales as required. Whilst the cloud is often cited as a great way to ensure scalability (which it certainly is) you have to "get it right" and that's what we do. Design and Development: Security is always important and the move to cloud poses some new challenges, least of all persuading the doubters. We have a solid understanding of the government security frameworks and experience in delivering pragmatic solutions that ensure accreditors remain happy. We are vendor neutral, but strongly support Open Source Software (OSS) and are keen to both leverage and deliver Open Data. Transition Management: Moving onto the cloud will be exciting and challenging, we work with you to make sure that no one and nothing gets left behind, ensuring that you have plan to cover issues such as data migration, user training, testing, service changeover and decommissioning. This should also cover important issues such as planning for any future "off boarding" to make best use of the supplier diversity and flexibility offered by G-Cloud. Some recent feedback from a supplier we worked with on a high profile cloud project was "You asked us some very hard questions, but you also had ideas and solutions for how we could respond"

In its Open Data White Paper "Unleashing the Potential", the Government outlined its serious intent to make public sector data more available to businesses and to the public. Where departments have identified candidate data Deloitte will design and deliver the change required. This may include delivery of infrastructure, tools, format transformation and data transformation. This change will be driven by the experience of our industry-leading experts in this field. The White Paper stated a principle that organisations should “Release data quickly, and then work to make sure that it is available in open standard formats, including linked-data forms.” The industry standard for measuring data availability is the 'Five Stars of Linked Open Data', specified by Sir Tim Berbers-Lee. The pinnacle of availability is consider to be a 5 star 'linked data' rating which indicates that the data is both available and is already linked to other data sources; allowing it to be easily exploited to generate insight. Whether it is the client's intention to transform to this level of maturity, or simply to make the data available on the web in its current form, Deloitte can scope, design and deliver the change needed.

TSO provides a highly-scalable, cloud-based, Enterprise-class, RDF storage platform and query engine. Offering full text search, geospatial and SPARQL 1.1 compliance, our triplestore already serves billions of triples. Our triplestore is part of the OpenUp® platform of services that can Harvest, Enrich, Store and Publish your data as Linked Open Data. The platform makes your data available in various formats to allow easy integration with existing applications. The format of data made available will reflect the query type, and can include SPARQL/XML, Json and RDF variants. TSO uses both 5Store and OWLIM for the provision of web-based RDF storage. These platforms are capable of scaling up to many billions of triples. column2: Getmapping White-Label Web GIS is an online mapping tool that can be branded and configured to suit your organisation. It can be used to plot information, create professional maps and share your business intelligence data. The software is suitable for organisations of any size and can be accessed from anywhere in the world, allowing easy remote, offsite and distributed working. The software is particularly popular with national environmental trusts, Local Authorities, Parish Councils and utilities. The software can complement your existing GIS infrastructure by providing additional users with an easy-to-use mapping interface, or it can become your primary GIS solution. The software makes managing mapping simple and efficient by providing an easy-to-use Admin interface to control users and layer styling. It also includes many pre-configured map layers that are maintained by Getmapping, removing the need to download and update these layers manually. For example, Natural England layers are kept up-to-date within the system. KEY FEATURES Built-in tools; Search, Print, Analyse, Annotate, Edit, Measure and Attach Files, among others. High resolution aerial photography for the UK built in Cloud Storage for your mapping at our high-performance UK-based Data Centre Professional assistance to help source and manage cost-effective map data KEY BENEFITS Out-of-the-box solution that can be fully deployed within 24 hours Brand it as your own product with your corporate logo and colour scheme Customised login page to fit in with your corporate design No investment in IT hardware, databases, software, development or maintenance Pre-configured Admin Panel to give you control of mapping, users, styling, tools and security TECHNICAL Import data using WMS, WFS, SHP, TAB, DXF or KML, or create new files Geocoding service to turn spreadsheets or databases into map data Supports all modern web browsers Continuous development of new tools, mapping, modules and 3rd party bolt-ons Over 99.9% system uptime INCLUDED Web GIS Map Interface with Search, Print, Measure, Edit and Attachment modules Web GIS Admin Panel A range of open mapping datasets, including Natural England, SNH, CCW, English Heritage, OS OpenData and BGS, among others PSMA and OSMA datasets (if licenced) Customer-side database links available for customers with 400+ users Getmapping WMS Collections available for customers with 400+ users

column2: Getmapping WMS Collections (Web Map Service) allows geographic base map data to be streamed over the web. It can be used as a cost-effective and efficient way of giving a whole organisation access to high quality map data, without the need for large local copies of the datasets to maintain in-house. With Getmapping WMS Collections, an organisation can remove the need to store and maintain their own copies of base mapping which saves time and frees IT resources and costs. Getmapping ensures all base maps are up-to-date which means each user can rely on the service to display the latest maps. It also ensures continuity over an organisation as each user is viewing the same version of the map. Getmapping WMS Collections: OS OpenData provides access to all the Ordnance Survey raster base maps available as OS OpenData. They are as follows; OS MiniScale, OS 1:250,000 Scale Colour Raster, OS VectorMap District and OS StreetView. Getmapping also value-adds the datasets to provide faded and greyscale versions of the mapping. The OS OpenData WMS Collection is a popular streaming product for large and small organisations as it provides a range of useful map scales that can underpin critical business operations at a very low annual cost. Getmapping WMS Collections can be connected to any OGC-compliant software package, or any WMS-compatible API. It can also be used directly within a web browser. Popular compatible software includes Pitney Bowes MapInfo Professional, ESRI ArcGIS, Quantum GIS, CadCorp SIS, Gaia and Getmapping GIS, among others. All Getmapping WMS Collections offer a 99.9% or greater service uptime and typical map load speeds range from less than 1 second on a Broadband connection up to 5 seconds on a mobile internet connection. These may vary depending on an organisation’s connection. Getmapping are very happy to provide demo accounts so the service can be tested on a customer’s own connection.

At Zennor Consulting we provide specialist advice, by security cleared consultants with a track record of delivery within central and local government for organisations looking to adopt or integrate cloud based solutions, which are increasingly being supplied by G-Cloud suppliers. 

Business Analysis: At the very early stages we can assist with the project concept, seeking to ensure your concept is "cloud ready" and that important issues are understood, such as the business impact levels of data and any pre-existing platforms that might need to be integrated or supported.  This leads on to requirements gathering, whilst both the spirit of G-Cloud and Agile ways of working do not embrace writing long lists of requirements up-front, there are still some important key criteria to get down on paper, such as business impact levels, estimated usage, integration requirements or "must have" functionality.

Project Selection and Specification: Selection of providers via G-Cloud is becoming more straightforward, however we can still help in running sifting through the service definitions, accreditation status and pricing tables in order to help with long listing, short listing and any detail required to identify the provider that most suits your project needs.

Design Authority: The cloud and G-Cloud open up a lot of opportunities regarding solutions, but the architecture within cloud solutions still needs to be defined correctly for any specific project and this is another area where we can help. This might involve meshing two or more cloud providers together, such as CDN and Web Hosting, designing in service separation so that services degrade gracefully under load or failure, or using cloud based testing and monitoring services to ensure the service scales as required. Whilst the cloud is often cited as a great way to ensure scalability (which it certainly is) you have to "get it right" and that's what we do.

Design and Development: Security is always important and the move to cloud poses some new challenges, least of all persuading the doubters. We have a solid understanding of the government security frameworks and experience in delivering pragmatic solutions that ensure accreditors remain happy. We are vendor neutral, but strongly support Open Source Software (OSS) and are keen to both leverage and deliver Open Data. 

Transition Management: Moving onto the cloud will be exciting and challenging, we work with you to make sure that no one and nothing gets left behind, ensuring that you have plan to cover issues such as data migration, user training, testing, service changeover and decommissioning. This should also cover important issues such as planning for any future "off boarding" to make best use of the supplier diversity and flexibility offered by G-Cloud.

Some recent feedback from a supplier we worked with on a high profile cloud project was "You asked us some very hard questions, but you also had ideas and solutions for how we could respond"

We offer a range of consultancy services around open data, particularly open government and public sector spending, budget and transactional data, including but not limited to data wrangling, developing and customising our flagship OpenSpending open source software to store, process and present open spending data, and training, research, strategy, licensing advice, and community building in the open data space.

column2: Enterprise Blueprints offer services covering: Agile Technical Architecture, Enterprise Architecture, Technical Strategy and Solution Architecture. Our service approach is to provide pragmatic and conformant solutions which represent excellent Value For Money (VFM). In particular they readily support the development of HM Treasury business cases and take account of HMG IT Strategy including GDS’sservice standards. Our service offering includes: • IT Landscape review including options for consolidation, rationalisation and modernisation • Assessment of business architecture maturity and alignment with IT agile delivery • High level assessment of alignment between business and technical/solution architectures • High level assessment of security and compliance architecture supporting Open Data • Review of transition from available ‘as-is’ to ‘to-be’ architectures including the use of open source and open standards to address cost and vendor lock-in identifying SMEs with service components • The use of modern infrastructure architectures to enable green IT and flexible service provision through cloud based solutions and the use of IAAS, PAAS and cloud (private, public) • The development of an assessment of the alignment between the business, technical architectures and the overarching information management strategy and information architecture which could enable provision of open data and use of big data Enterprise Blueprints have experience of conducting agile technical architecture work in IL3 environments and creating innovative outputs that have enabled clients to readily adopt novel initiatives and technical concepts delivered by agile, non-agile and hybrid methodologies, for example: • Technology and service roadmaps that exploit agile development mind-set and approaches • Integrated technology based services building out on HMG operating as the ‘SIAM’ providing coordinated commodity tower sourcing • Migration and integration of legacy environments to service oriented and agile delivery • Intelligent adoption of new technology (cloud, big data, social media, ... ) including assisted digital and providing services aligned to the GDS digital service standard • Operation under exacting compliance including: DPA, ICO, PCI/DSS, ISO27001/HMG IAMM and using frameworks such as ITIL V3 • Technological change as a means of gaining efficiency savings transition to increased green capability and delivery of flexible infrastructure provision Enterprise Blueprints have experienced architects and a range of highly competent and innovative experts to ensure engagement outputs are qualitatively sound and have practical relevance. All of the services are based on industry leading methods, aligning to the Agile agenda, standardised processes and tooling that are integrated within an accredited quality management system, including: • Strong governance which will be linked to the Client’s to ensure proper control • Industry standard architecture frameworks such as TOGAF, ITIL V3 • Qualified and competent in EA practice(s) evidenced by TOGAF and ITIL Certification and knowledgeable on HMG processes, governance and strategy implementation • Standard tooling that is available ‘on demand’ and is extensible for client use Each client will have a senior EB architect assigned as being responsible for all aspects of their account and direct access to an Enterprise Blueprints board member in the unlikely event that escalation is necessary.
